    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-04-12T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-04-12T04:00:00-05:00" n="793"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d793">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">684A.85/4–1254: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 793<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Egypt (<persName corresp="#p_CJ1"
                            type="from">Caffery</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d793fn1">Sent also to Tel Aviv priority; repeated to
                        Jerusalem.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-04-12T11:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 12, 1954—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1295. Re <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 1261.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d793fn2">See <ref target="#d787fn3">footnote 3, Document
                        787</ref>.</note> Embassy officer again emphasized to <persName
                        corresp="#p_RGM1">Riad</persName> yesterday our concern over incidents and
                    necessity avoid retaliation.</p>
                <p>Re military meeting with Israelis, <persName corresp="#p_RGM1">Riad</persName>
                    said as general principle Egypt always ready cooperate and never refuses
                    discussion. He said he would think about question his attending meeting and
                    might go <pb facs="1553" n="1513" xml:id="pg_1513"/> Gaza April 15 by <gloss
                        target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> plane if no new incidents. Meanwhile he is
                    recalling Colonel <persName corresp="#p_GLCS1">Gohar</persName> to take over his
                    work during his absence at Damascus April 18 meeting. <persName
                        corresp="#p_RGM1">Riad</persName> said agreements might be reached which
                    would stop major incidents for month or so but could never stop “individual
                    incidents” (i.e. thefts and exchanges of fire across line). He asserted Egyptian
                    retaliations were civilian while Israeli retaliations are organized either by
                        <gloss target="#t_IG1">IG</gloss> or border settlers over whom <gloss
                        target="#t_IG1">IG</gloss> has little or no control. He denied any
                    similarity to situation on Jordan border and concluded it is not matter of
                    agreements of which there are plenty, but of sincere cooperation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
